               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1019" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1019" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1019" type="surname" value="LAMB"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1019" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN LAMB</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the son of Joseph Lamb, who keeps a sale-shop.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184308210158"></xptr>
               <p>About the 5th of July the prisoner came to sell some clothes—I missed a handkerchief—it was safe when the prisoner came—when my father came home he missed it—this is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1020" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1020" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1020" type="surname" value="COX"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1020" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN COX</persName>
                  </hi>. About the 5th of July the prisoner gave me this handkerchief, and asked me to pawn it, which I did, at Mr. Grant's.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1021" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1021" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1021" type="surname" value="GUMNERS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1021" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL GUMNERS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable B</hi> 131.) I apprehended the prisoner. This handkerchief was given up to me at Queen-square—the pawnbroker said Cox brought it.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> There was another boy went into the shop; I did not see any handkerchief; when I came out I saw the boy again, and he sold it to me for 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; I had no money, and asked Cox to pawn it for me; he pawned it for 9<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., and I gave him 1 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</p>
               <p>
